<br>
Broke into Fear last night with one group.  60 DRU, 60 SHM, 60 RNG, 57 CLR, 56 ROG, 55 DRU.  Second Druid was there in case I went down.  We invised, jumped in, then ran to the SW ledge.  We fought a few mobs then evaced.  Rinsed and repeated until we cleared to the portal for others to come in.  Was a great sense of accomplishment as a Druid.  Guild went on to complete the Pally epic.<br>
<br>
Two days ago, we were doing the General in Kith for our Rogues.  No FDing monk high enough to split the pulls was around so in concert with a 60 Ranger, we Harmony pulled the camp.  After the Ranger left, and with one Rogue still to equip, I got the Druids together for a tag team.  Using 17 guild members and one badass non guild 60 warrior we turned the trick.  The three Druids each selected a mob in the camp and pulled.  One with help of a Shaman (lots of help) brought the General back to the group while the other two kited their mobs around to keep them out of the fight.  Four epics in one week - a big deal for our guild.<br>
<br>
Even though non of them went to us, it's been a good week for the Druids! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=rtfm>rtfm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/5/02 10:43:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ...</span><hr size=1> Interesting technique. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukulothar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kulothar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/10/02 7:58:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fear the Druids</span><hr size=1> hehe..  I get lots of practice running, snaring and rooting mobs for the Ring quest, Fear, General, etc.  I also do harmony pulls with the best on suits, wyverns, undead, etc. In Fear I have had too many mobs to count chasing me on breaks so the casters could camp.  I pull with rfs or FoR in Kael or SF on the summoners so they run faster back to camp.  It is fun to pull as a druid.<br>
<br>
Last night while camping RF I had to keep two crono, a drake, a wyvern and a wurm busy because the bard pulled and got two..  rather than bring them (we had 3 groups and no enc)  he kept running around and getting adds (Silly Bard)..   The cronos succeeded in striping all but my WF before I got them snared and rooted.   I also had a red Wurm snared and was leading around till a tank shot it with an arrow. It got mad and started summoning me (ouch.. Double 530 a hit).   <br>
<br>
